38
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,080
Why 60 and not 12?

39
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:29,320
Well, the traditional Chinese calendar is made up of two overlapping systems.

40
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:34,800
The animals of the zodiac are associated with what's called the 12 earthly branches, or

41
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,040
shaar, dijin.

42
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:42,880
Another system, the ten heavenly stems, or shiqingan, is linked with the five classical

43
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:52,280
elements of metal, dijin, wood, moo, water, shi, fire, hoa, and earth, tool.

44
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:57,560
Each element is assigned yin or yang, creating a ten-year cycle.

45
00:02:57,560 --> 00:03:02,040
When the twelve animals of the earthly branches are matched with the five elements, plus

46
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:07,960
the yin or the yang of the heavenly stems, it creates 60 years of different combinations,

47
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:11,560
known as a six-aginary cycle, or gangju.

48
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:17,160
So someone born in 1980 would have the sign of young metal monkey, while someone born

49
